a poem for the death of a baby can someone please help me find a perfect poem to send to my friend who's wife gave birth to a baby that died this is something i wrote on the death of my baby it's actually a song and you can email me for the musical version i took some quiet time today to put these words the perfect way they ve always been here in my heart i m just not sure where to start is it true oh can it be are you somewhere hearing me if i had your hand to hold you d be almost two years old and i look around my life and know that i won t ever let you go cause i see you in a cloudy day i see you in the bluest skies i ve seen you in your sister's smile i ve seen you in your father s eyes no matter how the years may pass or how my life may rain or shine you will always be with me i will hold your soul in mine they say time changes everyone there s nothing new under the sun to them my tears may be old news but they don t know you like i do when i look around my life and see your tiny fingers touching me cause i see you in a cloudy day i see you in the bluest skies i ve seen you in your brother s smile i ve seen you in your father s eyes no matter how the years may pass or how my life may rain or shine you will always be with me i will hold your soul in mine in my dreams i see you there the big blue eyes the soft brown hair the smiling face i almost knew but where are you where are you i took some quiet time today to put these words the perfect way Jon Secada Frankie Laine Hall & Oates Cliff Richard Wolfrider Similarities between the Bible and the Qur'an Kodocha The Beatles discography Care Bears Blood on the Tracks Paul Is Dead Phoebe Buffay's songs Unreleased Madonna songs Daryl Hall The McGuire Sisters Humphrey Bogart The Rock and Roll Hall of Fame's 500 Songs that Shaped Rock and Roll Shaggy dog story Wang Chongyang Liam Gallagher Carrie Jacobs-Bond Arjuna John Berryman Origin belief The Times They Are A-Changin' Bobby Caldwell The Beach Boys Little Snow Fairy S